{"title_page": "Askari Mohammadian", "text_new": "{{short description|Iranian wrestler}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=July 2017}}\n{{Infobox sportsperson\n|name=\n|nickname=\n|image =Askari Mohammadian.jpg\n| image_size     = 230px\n|caption=\n|birth_date= {{birth-date and age|2 March 1963}}\n|birth_place= [[Sari, Iran]]<ref name=sr/><ref name=r1/>\n| death_date = \n| death_place = \n| height = 170 cm\n| weight = \n|sport=[[Freestyle wrestling]]\n|event=\n|club= \n|coach=Rahim Tabrizi<ref name=r1/>\n|alma_mater= \n| show-medals    = yes\n| medaltemplates = \n{{MedalCountry | {{IRI}} }}\n{{MedalCompetition|[[Wrestling at the Summer Olympics|Olympic Games]]}}\n{{MedalSilver | [[1988 Summer Olympics|1988 Seoul]] | [[Wrestling at the 1988 Summer Olympics \u2013 Men's freestyle 57 kg|57 kg]]}}\n{{MedalSilver | [[1992 Summer Olympics|1992 Barcelona]] | [[Wrestling at the 1992 Summer Olympics \u2013 Men's freestyle 62 kg|62 kg]]}}\n{{MedalCompetition|[[FILA Wrestling World Championships|World Championships]]}}\n{{MedalSilver|[[1989 FILA Wrestling World Championships|1989 Martigny]]|57 kg}}\n{{MedalCompetition|[[Asian Games]]}}\n{{MedalGold| [[1986 Asian Games|1986 Seoul]] | [[Wrestling at the 1986 Asian Games|57 kg]]}} \n{{MedalSilver| [[1982 Asian Games|1982 New Delhi]] | [[Wrestling at the 1982 Asian Games|57 kg]]}} \n{{MedalCompetition|[[Asian Wrestling Championships|Asian Championships]]}}\n{{MedalGold|[[1983 Asian Wrestling Championships|1983 Tehran]]|57 kg}}\n{{MedalSilver|[[1989 Asian Wrestling Championships|1989 Oarai]]|57 kg}}\n}}\n\n'''Askari Mohammadian''' ({{lang-fa| \u0639\u0633\u06af\u0631\u06cc \u0645\u062d\u0645\u062f\u06cc\u0627\u0646}}, born 2 March 1963) is a retired [[Iran]]ian freestyle wrestler. He won gold medals at the 1983 Asian Championships and 1986 Asian Games, placing second at the 1982 Asian Games, 1988 and 1992 Olympics, 1989 world and 1989 Asian Championships.<ref name=sr/><ref name=iat/><ref name=r1/> His 1988 Olympic silver was the only medal for